Ethical hacking follows a structured process to identify and address security vulnerabilities. The five key stages of ethical hacking are:

1. Reconnaissance (Information Gathering)
This is the pre-attack phase, where the ethical hacker gathers as much information as possible about the target system. It can be active (direct interaction) or passive (indirect methods).

